    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I know how Petrie Terrace buyers shop. They have usually been looking through Paddington, Red Hill and Spring Hill for months and have decided that the small Petrie Terrace footprint, the heritage protection and the walkability are exactly what they want. They arrive at an open home with a clear picture of what the suburb's character cottages should look like, and pricing has to be honest about condition and floor plan.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The Caxton Street precinct gives Petrie Terrace its village heart, with restaurants, bars and Suncorp Stadium event nights all on the suburb's southern edge. The quieter lanes off Petrie Terrace itself and the streets running toward Hale Street consistently produce the strongest results for restored cottages with a usable rear courtyard or off-street parking. Heritage overlays mean supply is constrained: there is no easy path to subdivide or build new dwellings, which has supported a long-term scarcity premium for character homes that have been thoughtfully renovated.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229; border-radius:16px;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#191817; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Petrie Terrace Specialist</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">CBD-fringe character</p>
      </div>
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229; border-radius:16px;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#191817; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Walkable inner city</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Constrained heritage supply</p>
